com.paypal.selion.platform.dataprovider.impl

Class JsonDataProviderImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paypal.selion.platform.dataprovider.impl.JsonDataProviderImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SeLionDataProvider

    public final class JsonDataProviderImpl
extends Object
implements SeLionDataProvider
    This class takes care of parsing the test data given in the JSON format using the GSON library. The data returned is a 2D Array and there are utility methods to get specific data by index when not all data is required and convert a Json String to a specific type.

          Array Of Objects mapped to a user defined type:
 [
 {
  "name":"Optimus Prime",
  "password":123456,
  "accountNumber":999999999,

         "type" : "Savings",

                 }

  "phoneNumber":"1111111111",
  "preintTest":10

      • getDataAsHashtable

        public Hashtable<String,Object> getDataAsHashtable()
        A utility method to give out JSON data as HashTable. Please note this method works on the rule that the json object that needs to be parsed MUST contain a key named "id". 
         [
 {
  "id":"test1",
  "password":123456,
  "accountNumber":9999999999,
  "amount":80000,
  "areaCode":[{ "areaCode" :"area3"},
              { "areaCode" :"area4"}],
  "bank":{
         "name" : "Bank1",
         "type" : "Current",
         "address" : {
                     "street":"1234 dark St"
                 }
         }
 }
 ]
 Here the key to the data in the hashtable will be "test1"
        Specified by:
        getDataAsHashtable in interface SeLionDataProvider
        Returns:
        The JSON data as a Hashtable
